Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.610 --> 00:00:09.870
Welcome to Apache Junction Arizona, home to
the Lost Dutchman gold mine.

00:00:09.870 --> 00:00:16.460
Hi I'm Mike with Mike's Road Trip, and welcome
to Apache Junction, Arizona, a community located

00:00:16.460 --> 00:00:23.840
east of the Phoenix metro area, and home to
these, majestic Superstition Mountain.

00:00:23.840 --> 00:00:28.320
Where the legends and lore attract visitors
from around the world.

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:33.070
So come along with me, and let me show you
some of the area's attractions, events and

00:00:33.070 --> 00:00:35.870
businesses.

00:00:35.870 --> 00:00:39.730
Your visit to Apache Junction starts here,
at the Apache Junction Chamber of Commerce

00:00:39.730 --> 00:00:41.160
and visitor's center.

00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:51.149
Where you'll find attraction brochures, friendly
service, and even, a free cup of coffee.

00:00:51.149 --> 00:00:56.950
The Superstition Mountain Museum is the keeper
of all things legends and Lore in the area.

00:00:56.950 --> 00:01:07.320
They have structures from the old Apacheland
movie set as well as historic artifacts.

00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:13.790
Goldfield Ghost Town has something for everyone,
from shops, live music, horseback riding,

00:01:13.790 --> 00:01:17.600
to train rides, and even gun fights.

00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:21.820
(music playing)

00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:35.159
(sounds of gun fire)

00:01:35.159 --> 00:01:41.890
You'll also find Apache Trail Tours, a great
way to see the area and learn of its history.

00:01:41.890 --> 00:01:49.040
Up the hill from Goldfield is the historic
Mining Camp Restaurant and Dutchman's hideout,

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:59.189
where you'll find ol' west artifacts, live
entertainment and some tasty grub.

00:01:59.189 --> 00:02:04.680
Just past town you'll find Canyon Lake, a
recreational haven for water enthusiasts,

00:02:04.680 --> 00:02:10.580
and home, to the Dolly Steamboat.

00:02:10.580 --> 00:02:24.400
Down the road from Canyon Lake is the famed
Tortilla Flat, an icon destination for tourists.

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:31.550
Prospector Park is an amazing facility for
all kinds of sporting activities.

00:02:31.550 --> 00:02:37.840
Lost Dutchman State Park has one of the best
views of the Superstition Mountains.

00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:46.520
Arizona Opry is an AJ icon, providing variety
entertainment the whole family will enjoy.

00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:52.290
Arizona is well known for its golf, and there
are few places better than the Gold Canyon

00:02:52.290 --> 00:02:58.650
Golf Resort.

00:02:58.650 --> 00:03:10.599
(music playing)

00:03:10.599 --> 00:03:14.830
The city of Apache Junction has a state-of-the-art
library that is a great place to get connected,

00:03:14.830 --> 00:03:19.340
while researching the area attractions.

00:03:19.340 --> 00:03:23.940
Hog enthusiasts will enjoy Superstition Mountain
Harley, one of the biggest dealerships in

00:03:23.940 --> 00:03:26.700
the country.

00:03:26.700 --> 00:03:37.129
Apache Junction has also recently updated
and expanded it's college campus.

00:03:37.129 --> 00:03:42.110
The multi-generational facility is a fantastic
place to burn some calories.

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:46.860
From rock climbing, basketball court, full
workout facility.

00:03:46.860 --> 00:03:52.470
And, with these amazing views, you may never
want to leave.

00:03:52.470 --> 00:03:58.519
From the skate park, bike lanes, to endless
hiking and equestrian trails, recreational

00:03:58.519 --> 00:04:07.110
enthusiasts will rejoice.

00:04:07.110 --> 00:04:12.220
There are a slew of events here in Apache
Junction, including the annual Renaissance

00:04:12.220 --> 00:04:15.250
Festival.

00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:21.329
(Music playing)

00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:30.389
A flyover kicks off the annual Lost Dutchman
Days parade, one of the best in the state.

00:04:30.389 --> 00:04:37.909
(miner says: "There's gold back there in them
mountains")

00:04:37.909 --> 00:04:48.419
The annual Lost Dutchman Days is the signature
event for Apache Junction, Arizona.

00:04:48.419 --> 00:04:55.430
(music playing)

00:04:55.430 --> 00:05:13.169
Carnivals and rodeos round out just some of
the AJ annual events.

00:05:13.169 --> 00:05:18.139
Visitors and residents alike will appreciate
the various amenities the local businesses

00:05:18.139 --> 00:05:24.449
provide, from a number of exciting retirement
communities, health and wellness to shops

00:05:24.449 --> 00:05:33.919
and lodging.

00:05:33.919 --> 00:05:45.449
Well that's it from Apache Junction, Arizona,
home to the Superstition Mountains.

00:05:45.449 --> 00:05:47.840
Until next time, we'll see ya on the road
at MikesRoadTrip.com

